Research station A research station is a station that is built for the purpose of conducting scientific research. Research station sites might include remote areas of the world, oceans, as well as outer space, such as the International Space Station. Some research stations are located in the Arctic, such as the Northeast Science Station, McGill Arctic Research Station and Himadri Station. Some stations in the Arctic are manned drifting ice stations, built on the ice of the high latitudes of the Arctic Ocean. Many nations also have research stations located in Antarctica; Showa Station, Halley and Troll are examples. There
